727728f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - Yellowstone Boulevard
727728f-a.text:
GQueens Boulevard (trolley tracks thereon), east from Yellowstone
Boulevard (formerly White Pot Road; left foreground), showing an old
house remodeled and stuccoed in 1923. This is a set of two views.
This house was occupied for years by Charles Reitenbach, a blacksmith,
later by the Forrest Park Riding School.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

728257f-a.title: Queens: Yellowstone Boulevard - Queens Boulevard
728257f-a.text:
Yellowstone Boulevard, at the north side of this intersection
with lueens Boulevard, showing the Boerum farmhouse. This building
may still stand in a remodeled form (stucco). It was formerly on the
south side of the intersection of White Pot Road (cone in 1927) and
Hoffman Boulevard (nos part of Queens Boulevard.) John E. Backhus was
the owner in 1909.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
